title: Migos Allegedly Jumped Sean Kingston Tuesday Night In Las Vegas
text:
Home > Music > Migos Allegedly Jumped Sean Kingston Tuesday Night In Las Vegas Migos Allegedly Jumped Sean Kingston Tuesday Night In Las Vegas 0 0 Posted by Kevin Goddard , Feb 22, 2017 at 02:26am Migos apparently jumped Sean Kingston badly Tuesday night in Vegas. According to various reports online, it appears Migos & Sean Kingston got into a heated altercation Tuesday night at Las Vegas’ Agenda tradeshow that ended in gunfire. TMZ reports that Migos & Kingston got into it over an argument involving Soulja Boy , and the ATL trio ended up beating up Sean badly, allegedly stomping on his head & kicking him. Police say someone from Sean's crew pulled out a gun and fired a shot, but luckily no one was hit. That man has since been detained by security and turned over to the Vegas PD. By the time cops showed up, Migos & Sean fled the scene, but a short time later Sean was pulled over for a traffic violation and was "semi-co-operative," refusing to say names in the fight TMZ reports. Police say they're wanting to speak with the Migos, but they're not "wanted" by the cops. Check out a couple tweets/clips (below), and we’ll continue to keep you posted as more information surfaces. Sean Kingston jumped by the Migos in Vegas? There’s no sign of bad blood in this video. This was a few hours ago. ? 
(via. swaggcreator IG) pic.twitter.com/72Swi4iLu7 < class="robots-nocontent" rel=""> Feb 22, 2017 at 02:26am 1 View
